cs.IT, cs.ITP, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with information theory and distributed simulation, which are both covered by cs.IT and cs.ITP. The use of a dyadic decomposition scheme and the analysis of the entropy of a discrete common randomness variable suggest that the paper may also be relevant to cs.DS. The focus on simulating continuous random variables in a distributed manner suggests that the paper may be relevant to cs.SY. Finally, the use of log-concave pdfs and the analysis of a new measure of entropy suggest that the paper may also be relevant to cs.LG.
